hopobject.body: How do you do? viagra shopping Angela McVeigh, director of older people and primary care for the Southern Trust, said: "The trust arranges for over two million hours of domiciliary care to be provided to around 5,000 people in their own homes every year. This essential care to help people stay in their own homes is provided by either the trust's own staff or else by carers employed by a number of independent sector providers," she said.
